            <thetext>We&#39;ve had a problem where a unit test created a widget and destroyed it at the end of the test. The next test started before the dispose queue had disposed the widget which caused problems. The Test Runner should make sure the dispose queue is flushed at the end of each test, when tearDown is called to make sure tests don&#39;t influence each other in this way.</thetext>
